//********************************* Installment of Git for Windows *******************************//
1) open up link https://git-scm.com/download/win
2) Download 32 or 64-bit Windows Setup
3) Follow https://phoenixnap.com/kb/how-to-install-git-windows

Test Git 
1) open 
2) Hit Windows + X then press i when open (Opens Windows Powershell)
3) Go to desired directory and make a new directory called "repos" 

  command: mkdir repos 
  command: cd repos
  command: repos> git clone https://github.com/AlexeyAB/darknet.git 


//******************************* Installment of CUDA for Windows *******************************//

*CUDA is used for graphic card interface when training
*OpenCV is used for realtime computation predictions for model for both training and launching model

Check if your windows machine has a graphic cards by searching "device manager" 
Select "Display Adapter" and search if NVIDIA is presented
*Graphic card for training at the moment is NVIDIA GeForce GTX 1650 with Max-Q Design
If graphic card is present google "CUDA wiki" and under GPUs supported search the graphic card and note Computer Capability Version
*Our case is Version 7.5, meaing CUDA SDK 10.0/10.2 or lastest 11.0 will work
Search "CUDA <Version>" and download with settings: Windows + x86_64 + Version 10
Following the window prompts until done installing

Test CUDA
1) Follow https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-quick-start-guide/index.html


